{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe 2026-07-08 principal-architect audit (Reliability finding #3) found that three documented reconciler safety mechanisms are implemented, tested, and **never called in production** — the safety they promise is illusory, and the current epic's children do not cover them:\n\n1. **Create→label crash window double-creates Jira issues.** `dispatch_one.py:241-256` runs `create_issue` → then adds the `rebar-id:` label the JQL dedup keys on → then binds in memory only; bindings persist only at end of pass (`reconcile.py:1068`). A hard crash between create and label leaves an orphan issue invisible to dedup; the re-run creates a duplicate.\n2. **The write-ahead/recovery protocol is dead code — and miswired.** `binding_store.py:6-16` documents pending→confirm; `bind_pending` has zero production callers, and `run_differs.py:267` passes the applier module (which has no `search_issues`) as the client to `recover_pending_bindings`, so real recovery would `AttributeError` into a fail-open swallow (`run_differs.py:268-274`).\n3. **Crashed pass deadlocks reconciliation forever.** Lease `steal()` is implemented and tested (`_ref_lock.py:470-533`) but the held-ref path unconditionally exits 3 (`__main__.py:534-539`); after a SIGKILL the remote `refs/reconciler/lock` persists until an operator hand-deletes it.\n4. **All three retry layers are inert.** The REST helper re-raises every `HTTPError` (`acli_rest.py:61-63`); `_call_with_backoff` (`acli_subprocess.py:236-292`) has zero production call sites; the applier's `_call_with_retry` only retries `JiraAPIError`, which nothing in the client layer raises (`dispatch_one.py:100-144`). Sibling C4 (lambswool-shaded-eider) fixes only the bulk-path 429 parity — it does not revive these layers.\n\n## What\n\nWire each mechanism into its intended call site, smallest-change-first:\n\n1. **Revive the retry layer WITHOUT a boundary translation.** Do NOT translate `HTTPError`→`JiraAPIError` at\n   `acli_rest.py` — that would silently break the 8+ callers that catch raw `urllib.error.HTTPError` from the REST\n   path (outbound_differ.py:134, apply_handlers.py:147/151 — which explicitly needs raw 404, acli_graph.py:259/360/454,\n   fetcher.py:445/491/528, inbound_probe.py:107, acli_cli_ops.py:136, dispatch_one.py:484, applier.py:752). Instead,\n   extend the applier's `_call_with_retry` (dispatch_one.py:100-144) to ALSO recognize a retryable\n   `urllib.error.HTTPError` (429 with `Retry-After`; 5xx with jittered backoff) in addition to `JiraAPIError`,\n   leaving acli_rest's raw-`HTTPError` raise UNCHANGED. Non-retryable statuses (4xx except 429) propagate raw exactly\n   as today. This revives retry/backoff for the wrapped write path with ZERO blast radius on the raw-HTTPError\n   callers. (`_call_with_backoff` in acli_subprocess.py stays out of scope — C4 owns the bulk 429 path.)\n2. **Write-safety via a per-retry dedup guard (not generic re-invoke).** `_call_with_retry` re-invokes the same\n   callable; the JQL dedup search (dispatch_one.py:196) runs ONCE before the wrapper, so a mid-flight 429/5xx on\n   `create_issue`/`add_comment` could re-send and double-create. Wrap each non-idempotent op in a dedup-aware\n   callable that RE-RUNS the rebar-id JQL search (create) / comment-marker check (comment) at the START of every\n   retry attempt and short-circuits to the existing issue/comment if the dedup key now exists — so a retry after a\n   possibly-succeeded write never duplicates. Idempotent ops (update/transition/label) retry directly.\n3. **Write-ahead recovery.** Call `bind_pending` + persist the binding store **before** `create_issue`, confirm\n   after label attach; fix `recover_pending_bindings` (run_differs.py:267) to receive a real client exposing\n   `search_issues` (not the applier module), and make recovery failures LOUD (alert + nonzero manifest tally)\n   instead of the current fail-open `AttributeError` swallow (run_differs.py:268-274).\n4. **Crashed-pass lease steal.** In `__main__.py`'s held-lock path (`__main__.py:534-539`), invoke `steal()` when\n   the lease is EXPIRED (fence semantics already implemented at `_ref_lock.py:470-533`); keep exit 3 for a live,\n   unexpired holder.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `dispatch_one.py` (`_call_with_retry` HTTPError-aware + dedup-guarded write callables + bind_pending-before-create),\n`run_differs.py` (recover_pending_bindings client fix + loud failures), `__main__.py` (lock-path steal), plus tests\nunder `tests/scripts/bridge/` and `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/`. Read-only (relied on, not changed): `acli_rest.py`\n(raw HTTPError raise UNCHANGED — verified non-breaking for its 8+ catchers), `binding_store.py` (`bind_pending`/\n`recover_pending_bindings` already implemented). Out: bulk-path 429 parity (C4 owns it), inbound status mapping\n(audit-remediation epic), any refactor of the retry helpers' structure, `_call_with_backoff` revival (C4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_call_with_retry` retries a retryable `HTTPError` (simulated 429 with `Retry-After` honored; simulated 500 with jittered backoff) — WITHOUT translating at `acli_rest.py`; a test asserts the raw `HTTPError` raise from `acli_rest` is unchanged so the 8+ raw-`HTTPError` catchers (e.g. apply_handlers.py:151's 404 path) still see raw `HTTPError`.\n- [ ] Non-idempotent writes (create/comment) re-run their dedup key check (rebar-id JQL / comment marker) at the START of every retry attempt and short-circuit if the key now exists — a test injects a 429 AFTER a create that already landed and asserts NO duplicate issue is created.\n- [ ] `bind_pending` is written and the store persisted before `create_issue`; a crash injected between create and label leaves a pending record that the next pass recovers via a working `search_issues` client (no duplicate issue)\n- [ ] `recover_pending_bindings` receives a client object exposing `search_issues`; a recovery failure raises an alert and a nonzero manifest tally instead of a silent swallow\n- [ ] A pass encountering an expired lease steals it via `steal()` and proceeds; a live unexpired lease still exits 3 (both covered by tests)\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/scripts/bridge/ -q` green"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783565108054641001,"uuid":"8e2836e9-cc37-4768-a26e-96b22bc5c90c"}